FBIS4-29470 "dreas118__a94019" FBIS-EAS-94-118-A Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan SDPJ: Party's To Propose Broad Coalition SDPJ: Party's To Propose Broad Coalition OW1706144094 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 17 Jun 94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1706144094 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] Speaking at a lecture in Tokyo on the afternoon of 16 June, Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] General Secretary Wataru Kubo touched on a coalition blueprint the SDPJ plans to submit as early as next week. He said: "Even if we place our policies highly, this does not always meet the people's expectations. Our policies should be broad ones that can win the support of the various coalition parties." In this way, he indicated his view that in hammering out the party's alliance proposal, the party will give priority to basic agreements reached with the ruling parties.
